ruby-mkrf
------------------------------------------
mkrf is a Ruby module used to generate Rakefiles for Ruby extension 
modules. It is intended as a replacement for mkmf.

Runtime requirements:
  ruby-1.8.6-1
  ruby-rake-0.7.2-1
  rubygems-0.9.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygport-0.3.10-1

Canonical website:
  http://mkrf.rubyforge.org/

Canonical download:
  http://rubyforge.org/projects/mkrf/files

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ruby-mkrf-0.2.3-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ruby-mkrf-0.2.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ruby-mkrf-0.2.3-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ruby-mkrf-0.2.3-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/lib/ruby/site_ruby/1.8/mkrf.rb
  /usr/lib/ruby/site_ruby/1.8/mkrf/availability.rb
  /usr/lib/ruby/site_ruby/1.8/mkrf/generator.rb
  /usr/lib/ruby/site_ruby/1.8/mkrf/rakehelper.rb
  /usr/share/doc/ruby-mkrf-0.2.3/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/ruby-mkrf-0.2.3/README

------------------

Port Notes:

